7. The script will auto-increment the version based on existing files in `~/Downloads/`. **CRITICAL**: You MUST read the stdout of the script to find the actual generated filename (e.g., `SUCCESS: Presentation saved to ...v64.pptx`) and provide that EXACT path to the user. Do not guess the output filename.

### Auto-agenda slide (slide 2) — **no code on screen**

The Slide Deck MCP **injects** an agenda immediately after the TITLE slide. The engine derives lines from your spec (typically **Section Title** slides and/or slide titles). **Known failure mode:** if a **`paragraphs[].text`** field is a **JSON array of run objects** (e.g. `[{"text":"PESTEL","font_size_pt":11,"color":"laptop"}]`), some builds **`str()` that list** into the agenda shape → the audience sees Python-like `[{'text': 'PESTEL', ...}]` instead of readable copy.

**Mandatory (Section Title / divider slides):**

1. **Anti-Extraction Pattern:** Use **`"text": "S E C T I O N  [NN]\n[Section Name]"`** as a single plain string for the entire text box. **Never** use a `paragraphs` array. This prevents the auto-agenda from extracting malformed JSON.
2. **v65 minimalist subtitle style:** Keep the Section Name **SHORT** (2-4 words maximum) matching v65 format: `"Research challenge"`, `"PESTEL"`, `"Competitive landscape"`, `"Primary research"`, `"Thematic analysis"`, `"Win / Loss"`. Do NOT use verbose pipe-separated descriptions (e.g., "Research challenge | Research questions, objectives, and Braun & Clarke...").

**Examples (v65-compliant Section Names):**

- `"text": "S E C T I O N  0 1\nResearch challenge"` (NOT "Research challenge | Research questions, objectives...")
- `"text": "S E C T I O N  0 2\nPESTEL"` (NOT "PESTEL | Political, economic, social...")
- `"text": "S E C T I O N  0 3\nPrimary research"` (NOT "Primary research | Interview programme, participant roster...")
- `"text": "S E C T I O N  0 4\nCompetitive landscape"` (NOT "Competitive landscape | Regional specialists vs global platforms")
- `"text": "S E C T I O N  0 5\nThematic analysis"` (NOT "Thematic analysis | Validated themes and triangulation")

**Checklist:** Open the output `.pptx` slide 2; if any line contains `[{` or `'text':`, revise **Section Title** `paragraphs` to plain-string `text` and richer copy, then regenerate.

**Custom agenda formatting**: For PMF roadmap decks presented to executives, apply the explicit agenda pattern from **010-style-guide.mdc → Agenda Slide Formatting Standards** (14pt font, Section Title layout with branded panel). Insert as explicit slide 2 to override MCP auto-generation.

## Slide spec schema (mandatory — matches `user-slide-deck-mcp` `create_presentation`)

**Typography and layout standards**: See **`010-style-guide.mdc` → Deck Generation → Typography Standards** for canonical font sizing, body box dimensions, color palette, and bullet formatting.

**130-specific schema rules:**

- Use **`layout_name`** on every slide (e.g. `"TITLE"`, `"Title Only"`, `"Title Only_Alt"`, `"Section Title"`, `"1/2 Headline_Alt"`, `"Bumper Slide"`). Do **not** use a top-level `"layout"` key; the engine ignores it and may render every slide as a title slide.
- **`placeholders`** must map indices to objects: `"0": {"text": "Title"}`. Never use `"0": "plain string"`.
- **Section Title** has no title placeholder. **CRITICAL**: Follow **`010-style-guide.mdc` → Section Title Slides (Anti-Extraction Pattern)** EXACTLY:
  - Use **`"text": "S E C T I O N  [NN]\n[Section Name]"`** format with plain string (NOT paragraphs array)
  - Example: `"text": "S E C T I O N  0 2\nPESTEL Analysis"`
  - Section Name in TITLE CASE, SHORT (2-4 words: "PESTEL Analysis", "Primary Research", "Win / Loss Analysis")
  - FORBIDDEN: Using "Workday Confidential" text in Section Title slides
  - FORBIDDEN: Using `paragraphs` array in Section Title slides (triggers agenda extraction and allows "Workday Confidential" anti-pattern)
  - Only use placeholders if you want that text in the auto-generated agenda
- **Body content:** Prefer **`text_boxes[].paragraphs`** with **`level`: 1** for bullets (native `•`) instead of a single **`text`** string with Unicode bullet characters. Per-paragraph and per-run formatting supports **`font_size_pt`**, **`bold`**, **`highlight`** (e.g. PESTEL **Product implication:** `FFFF00`).

**Agenda formatting**: For executive PMF roadmap presentations, apply the custom agenda pattern from **010-style-guide.mdc → Agenda Slide Formatting Standards** (14pt font, Section Title layout with branded panel). Insert as explicit slide 2 to override MCP auto-generation when presenting to leadership.

**PESTEL slide titles (v65 style):**
- Use factor name only: "Political", "Economic", "Social", "Technological", "Environmental", "Legal"
- Do NOT add "PESTEL -" prefix (the section divider already establishes PESTEL context)

**Slide title length constraints (MANDATORY ENFORCEMENT)**: ALL slide titles must follow **010-style-guide.mdc → Slide Title Length Standards**:
- **Hard limit**: 45 characters (including spaces) — titles exceeding this WILL wrap to 2 lines
- **Target**: 40 characters or fewer — ensures reliable single-line fit
- **Word limit**: 6-8 words maximum

**BEFORE writing slides_spec JSON** (MANDATORY PRE-GENERATION VALIDATION): 
1. Draft all slide titles in a list
2. Count characters for EVERY title (including spaces)
3. REWRITE ANY title ≥45 chars using 010 guidance:
   - Lead with key insight or takeaway
   - Remove filler: "Overview of", "Introduction to", "Analysis of", "Discussion on"
   - Use colons or hyphens for context (not " | ")
   - Abbreviate: "Practices & Guidelines" not "Practices and Guidelines"
4. FLAG titles 40-45 chars for optional tightening (recommended for polish)
5. Only proceed to JSON generation after ALL titles are ≤45 chars

**Title rewriting examples:**
- ❌ "Customer Interviews | 3 GCC-market enterprise participants (semi-structured)" (78 chars) 
  ✅ "1:1 Customer Interviews - GCC Enterprise" (42 chars)
- ❌ "Customer Research Programme - GCC Enterprise" (47 chars, wraps in practice)
  ✅ "1:1 Customer Interviews - GCC Enterprise" (42 chars)
- ❌ "Win / Loss Analysis - GCC-Relevant and EMEA Proxy Gaps" (55 chars)
  ✅ "Win/Loss - GCC & EMEA Proxy Gaps" (33 chars, cleaner)


