## Deck structure summary (v65 parity ~50–60 slides)

**MANDATORY:** Unless the user asks for a **focus deck**, implement every section below. **Full specs, examples, and enforcement detail:** `docs/decks/130-slide-section-reference.md`.

| Order | Section | Slide target (typical) | Key constraints (see reference for full rules) |
|-------|---------|------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| 1 | Title + Executive Summary | 2–3 | Subtitle = `[Month YYYY]` only; Executive Summary max 4 bullets × 200–250 chars; split across two slides if needed. |
| 2 | Research Challenge | 2 + divider | Objectives and methodology; **no** "5-Phase Framework" slide. |
| 3 | Context Review | 2 + divider | **Two slides** ("Why [Region] Now" + "Market Momentum"); do not merge. |
| 4 | Product Strategy | 1–3 + divider | Only if `strategy-context-*.md` exists; verify Step 1 sources; non-GCC decks: **focal region first** on Q2 and Regional Expansion slides. |
| 5 | PESTEL Analysis | 7 + divider | **Source:** @product-strategy-agent `pestel-analysis-*.md` only; factor titles without "PESTEL -" prefix; depth, anchors, Product implication per reference. |
| 6 | Competitive Landscape | 3 + divider | Regional + Global as **tables** (not bullets); SWOT from @product-strategy-agent `swot-analysis-*.md` only; single 2×2 table, 9pt, semicolon-separated cells. |
| 7 | Win/Loss Analysis | 3 + divider (or no-data variant) | No Dataset Overview; chart by **gap theme**; if no 108 rows, single data-availability slide only. |
| 8 | Customer Ideation Hub | 3 + divider (or DATA GAP) | No "AI Ideas Spotlight"; "Ideation Hub: Key Themes" format per reference. |
| 9 | Internal SME Interviews | 3–7 + divider, conditional | After Ideation, before Primary Research; SME1… on slides; real names **speaker notes only**. |
| 10 | Primary Research | Intro + table + 1 slide per Pn | Executive intro bullets; per-customer quote/JTBD minima per reference. |
| 11 | Thematic Analysis | 2–3 grouped + matrix | **Not** one slide per theme; triangulation table; density caps per reference. |
| 12 | Full Funnel / Gap Analysis | 1–2 | Title **"Gap Analysis"**; **table** mandatory; Deployment Agent validation per reference. |
| 13 | Roadmap Recommendations | ≤5 + divider (+ E2E summary table when applicable) | Five-part slides (Problem → Evidence → Recommendation → Why now → Success metrics); executive wording for roadmap summary table. **Success Metrics MUST include a specific, quantified target with baseline and improvement (e.g., '30% reduction on pilot requisitions versus control groups'). Vague metrics like 'improve efficiency' or 'increase adoption' are FORBIDDEN.** **Why Now MUST reference at least one of: Q2 strategic priority, OKR target, competitive pressure with named competitor, or regulatory deadline. Generic urgency ('customers are asking') is insufficient.** |
| 14 | Bumper Slide | 1 | Standard close. |

**Inventory alignment:** Prefer `docs/decks/gcc-pmf-roadmap-v65-slide-inventory.md` as skeleton. Do not skip SWOT, Win/Loss block (or DATA GAP), Ideation block (or DATA GAP), or Full Funnel unless **focus deck**. Full decks claiming v65 parity: **≥36** slides minimum; **~50–60** target.

